> Compaq Servers come with hot pluggable PCI slots.. can you 
> re-scan the PCI
> bus once linux has booted? Or would this cause probs?
I don't think you can rescan the bus, but what you can do is hot-replace a
card. ie If your nic breaks you could hot-swap it with an identical nic, and
insert the driver again.
incidentally, this is no more than what NT4 can do on Compaq hardware.
regards,
-paul jakma.
